Rating: 3
When I brought turkey tenderloins home from the marked-down section at my supermarket, I came to epicurious.com to see what I might do with them. OH MY GOSH, this was THE answer! DELICIOUS, and so very easy (unless you count that I never quite got the hang of skewering the sides together with toothpicks. So I cooked them in a casserole dish tilted up a bit so all the cheese and pesto wouldn't run out.) NOTES: I did cook a bit longer to get the temp up to 160. And I subbed Jarlsberg for Provolone. I debated on 4 forks, so don't be let down by my "3" rating! Served with stuffed tomatoes, and steamed veggies (grn bns, crookneck squash, onions). Would serve to company for my most elegant of meals!

